<P>Pardons were al&s;o granted by the bi&s;hop and his predece&s;&s;ors for felonies, out|lawries, and tre&s;pa&s;&s;es, <HI>contra pacem,</HI> and forfeitures for recognizances. The
<PB N="291" REF="338">lands, chattels, and effects, of per&s;ons accountant to the bi&s;hop, were &s;eized for defaults; and inqui&s;itions were awarded touching all public tre&s;pa&s;&s;es<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>De Ter. Ten. Bonis &amp; Catall que fuere R. de Whitparis in man. D' n'i &s;ei&s;iend.</HI> Sched. 13. A^o x^o.
<P>R. Dei gra. &amp;c. Vicecom. Dun. S. Quia Ric'us de Whitparis capitalis fore&s;tarius n'r de Werdale qui in div'&s;is pecuniar. &s;u'mis nob. tenetur &amp; qui de exitibus ballive compu' &s;uum non nondu' reddidit, die' clau&s;it extremum, &s;icut ex te&s;timonio accepim. fide digno. Tibi precepimus q'd o'ia Ter. &amp; Ten. de quibus idem R. fuit &s;eitus in denico &s;uo quecu'qu' ut de feodo die obit. &s;ui, ac etiam bena &amp; catalla &s;ua quecu'q' in quorcuq' manibus inventa in ballia tua &s;ine dilac'oe capias in man. n'ram &amp; ea &s;alvo &amp; &s;ecure ab&s;q' di&s;|trac'coe aliqua cu&s;todiri fac. Ita q'd nullus ad ea. manus aliqualiter apponat, fine mandato n'ro &s;p'iali quou&s;q' de eo quod nob. in hac p'te debetur p'ut decet, &amp; rondeatur, &amp; aliud a nob. inde hu'eris in man|datis. Et hoc ficut te indempnem erga nos co'&s;ervare volueris nullatenus omittas. Dat. Dun. &amp;c.</P>
<P><HI>Carta de P'don utlagar.</HI> Sched. 14. A^o x^o.</P>
<P>R. Dei gra. &amp;c. O'ib's ballivis &amp; fidelib's &s;uis ad quos, &amp;c. S. &s;ciatis q'd cu. Andreas de Merkyngfeld chiv. p' eo q'd nup' non venit cora' dil'cis &amp; fid. n'ris Rog'o de Efsh &amp; &s;ociis &s;uis tunc ju&s;tic. n'ris ad qua|dam tran&s;gre&s;&s;ionem Elie, &amp;c. P'p'fatu Andream &amp; alios ut dicitur, illatam audiend. &amp; t'minand. a&s;&s;ign. ad ro'ndendu p'fatis Elie, &amp;c. de t'ngre&s;&s;ione p'd'ca in exigend po&s;itus fui&s;&s;et in com. Sadberg. ad utlagand. &amp; ea occ'one p't modum utlagatus, ut accepimus. Nos ad requi&s;ico'em dil'ci &amp; fidelis n'ri Ric'i de Alde|burgh p'donavimus eidem Andree utlagarium figna in ip'um occ'one p'mi&s;&s;a fuerit p'mulgata &amp; firma' pa|cem n'ram ei inde co'cedimus. Ita tamen q'd &s;tet recto in cur. n'ra &s;i p'd'ci Elias, &amp;c. v'&s;us eum loqui vo|luerunt de t'ngre&s;&s;ione &s;up'a dicta. In cujus, &amp;c.</P>
