<PB N="335" REF="382">
<P>In this prelate's time, prior John de Hemmingburg died, and John We&s;&s;ington was elected his &s;ucce&s;&s;or.</P>
<P>The cardinal departed this life on the 20th day of No|vember, A. D. 1437, and was interred, agreeable to the directions of his will, dated 21&s;t Dec. A. D. 1436, in the chantry, founded by him, as before mentioned, in the gallile. A table of marble is placed on his tomb, on the foot of which his coat armour is &s;culptured as in the margin, but no in&s;cription.</P>
