<PB N="364" REF="411">
<P>In 1482 he granted his licence to the prior of Durham to purcha&s;e in mort|main<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">Licentia p. (Roberto) pr. Dun. de terr. adquirend.&mdash;Dudley, Rot. A. N^o 70.
<P>"Quod ip'i &amp; &s;ucce&s;. &s;ui ter. &amp;c. ad valor. 20 librar. que de nob. non tenenturp. &s;ervic. militare ac|quirere, &amp;c. &s;tatuto de terr. &amp; ten. ad manum mortuam non ponend. edito non ob&s;tante dum tamen per inqui&s;iciones inde in forma debita capiendas &amp; in cancellar. n'ra &amp; &s;ucc. n'ror retornand. compertum &s;it quod id fieri po&s;&s;it ab&s;q. damno vel, &amp;c. n'ro &amp; &s;ucc. n'ror, 10 Oct. 1482."</P>
