<P>Mortizacio div'&s;ar. terrar. &amp; ten. p. pr. Dun. acqui&s;it. p. licentiam." Rot. B. N^o 77.&mdash;Randal's MSS.</P></NOTE>. In 1483 he licen&s;ed the rector of Houghton-le-Spring, to embattle and fortify the tower of his rectory-hou&s;e<NOTE N="&dagger;" PLACE="foot">Lic. J. Kelyng, cl. r'coris de Houghton de quad. turre infra r'coriam ibid. batelland. 6 Oct. 1483. Rot. Dudley, A. N^o 87.&mdash;See Houghton-le-Spring in vol. ii.</NOTE>; and the &s;ame year granted a licence to Ralph lord Nevill, and dame I&s;abell his wife, to found a chauntry in the church at Brauncepeth<NOTE N="&Dagger;" PLACE="foot">Rot. A. Dudley, N^o 94. 20 Sept. 1483. <HI>Commi&s;&s;ion of enquiry after wreck of the &s;ea.</HI>&mdash;"Hugoni Smell &amp; Johanni Goodyer legum doctoribus &amp; aliis, ad inquirend. de navifract. &amp; re&s;tituend. bona navis inxta Hartinpole ver&s;us Thomam Lumley dominum de Lumley, &amp; alios qui navem &amp; bona fregerunt, &amp;c." Rot. A. Dudley, 17 Ed. IV. 1477.
