<PB N="401" REF="450">the cardinal was nominated guardian of the temporalties of this See, and in the &s;ame month appointed thereto, re&s;igning on that occa&s;ion the bi&s;hopric of Bath and Wells; and he received re&s;titution of the temporalties on the 30th day of April 1523<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">W. de Chambre.&mdash;Angl. Sac. p. 782.&mdash;Rot. Tho. Card. A. N^o 1.&mdash; II. Octavus, d. g. &amp;c. Sciatis, q'd cu. epat. D. p. mortem bone memorie Tho. nup. e'pi ib'm vacav'it, &amp; modo vacans exi&s;tat, nos de gr'a n'ra &s;p'ali, &amp;c. ded. &amp; conce&s;&s;imus, &amp;c. rev'endi&s;&s;imo in Xr'o p'ri Tho. &amp;c. cu&s;todiam d'e'i e'patus Dun. ae o'iu. t'p'alium eju&s;d. neenon o'iu. ca&s;tror. d'inor. man'ior. terrar. ten. reddit. &s;ervicior. porco'um, pen&s;ionu. annui|tat. &amp; aliar. &amp;c. conce&s;imus etiam, &amp;c. o'ia &amp; o'i'od. feod. milit. &s;'vicia, warda, maritagia, &amp; cu&s;todiam o'iu. ho'ium quor'cumque, &amp;c. Et in&s;up. concedimus pref. &amp;c. plena. pot. &amp; auct. no'i'andi, &s;aciendi, &amp; con&s;$$|tuendi canc. ju&s;tic. vic. e&s;caetores, coronatores, &s;en'los, ballivos, ac o'es &amp; &s;ig'los min. alios officia$io$, &amp;c. quoad exercenda regalia ib'm eid, e'patu ab antiquo debit &amp; pertin, adeo libere, plene, &amp; integre p'nt p't. Tho. &amp;c. aut aliquis al. predec. &s;uis, &amp;c. conce&s;&s;im. etiam. &amp;c. o'i'od. advocac'o'es, donac o'es, p'&s;entac' o|'es, &amp;c. Et ult'ius, &amp;c. ded. &amp; conce&s;&s; &amp;c. o'ia &amp; &s;ig'la exitus &s;irmas redditus, &amp;c. habend. &amp;c. ad u&s;u. p'prin. &amp;c. ab&s;q comp'o. aut aliquo alio nob. inde reddend. vel &s;aciend. &amp;c.&mdash; Randal's MSS.
