<P>On the 26th of December, 1560, a <HI>Cong&egrave; d'Elire</HI> was granted for electing a bi&s;hop in the room of Tun&s;tall deprived; on which occa&s;ion, JAMES PILKINGTON was duly cho&s;en by the dean and chapter, and received the royal a&s;&s;ent on the 20th of February following. He was con&s;ecrated on the 2d day of March; had the temporalties re&s;tored on the 25th of the &s;ame month, with &s;ome exceptions; and was in&s;talled the 10th day of April, 1561. As this is the fir&s;t election after the di&s;&s;olution of the mona&s;tery, the &s;everal in&s;truments are given at length in the notes<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot"><HI>The Conge d'Elire to elect a Bi&s;hop.</HI>
<P>REGINA, dilectis &s;ibi in Chri&s;to, decano et capitulo eccle&s;iae cathedralis Dunolmen&s;is, &s;alutem. Ex par$e ve&s;tra nobis e&s;t humiliter &s;upplicatum, ut cum eccle&s;ia praedicta per legitimam deprivationem ultimi epi&s;co|pi eju&s;dem, jam vacet et pa&s;toris &s;it &s;olatio de&s;tituta, alium vobis eligendi in epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem, licenti|am no&s;tram fundatoriam vobis concedere dignaremur. Nos precibus ve&s;tris in hac parte favorabiliter incli|nati, licentiam illam vobis duximus concedendam; rogantes quod talem vobis eligatis in epi&s;copum et pa&s;to|rem, qui Deo devotus, nobi&s;&abque; et regno no&s;tro utilis et fidelis exi&s;tat. In cujus rei, &amp;c. Te&s;te regina apud We&s;tmona&s;terium, 26 die Decembris 1560.&mdash;Ryme's Foedera, vol. xv. p. 605.</P>
<P><HI>The Queen's approbation of Dr Pilkington.</HI></P>
<P>REGINA, reverendi&s;&s;imo in Chri&s;to patri, et praedilecto et fideli no&s;tro domino Thomae archiepi&s;copo Eborum, ac aliis quibu&s;cumque epi&s;copis quorum in hac parte intererit, &s;alutem. Cum vacante nuper &s;ede epi&s;e. eccle&s;iae cathedralis Dunelm. per legitimam deprivationem ultimi epi&s;copi eju&s;dem, ad humilem peti|tionem decani et capituli eccle&s;iae no&s;trae cathedralis Dunelm. per literas no&s;tras patentes, licentiam conce&s;|&s;erimus alium &s;ibi eligendi in epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem &s;edis praedictae, iidemque decanus et capitulum, vigore et obtentu licentiae no&s;trae praedictae, dilectum nobis in Chri&s;to, Jacobum Pylkington &s;acrae theologiae bac|cularium, &s;ibi et eccle&s;iae praedictae elegerunt in epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem, prout per literas &s;uas &s;igillo eorum communi &s;igillatas, nobis inde directas, plenius liquet et apparet: Nos, electionem illam acceptantes, eidem electioni regium no&s;trum a&s;&s;en&s;um adhibuimus pariter et favorem, et vobis tenore prae&s;entium &s;igni&s;icamus. Rogantes, ac in fide et dilectione quibus nobis tenemini, firmiter praecipiendo mandantes, quatenus vos cun|dem Jacobum Pylkington in epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem eccle&s;iae praedictae, &s;ic ut prae&s;ertur electum, electionem|que praedictam confirmare, et eundem Jacobum Pylkington in epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem eccle&s;iae cathedralis Dunolmen&s;. praedictae con&s;ecrare, caetera&abque; omnia et &s;ingula peragere, quae ve&s;tro in hae parte incumbunt $&s;licio pa&s;torali, juxta formam &s;tatutorum in ea parte editorum et provi&s;oru' velitis cum favore. In cujus $$i te&s;timonium, &amp;c. Te&s;te regina apud We&s;tmona&s;terium vice&s;imo die Februarii, 1561&mdash;Rymer's Foe|d$ra, vol. xv. p. 607.</P>
<P><HI>Re&s;titution of the Temporalties.</HI></P>
<P>REGINA, e&s;caetori &s;uo in comitatu Eborum, &s;alutem. Vacante $uper epi&s;$opatu Dunolmen&s;i, per de|p$$vationem Cuthberti Tun&s;tall ultimi epi&s;copi ibidem, decanus et capitulum eccle&s;iae cathedralis Dunolm. $$$dictae, licentia no&s;tra petita patiter et obtenta, dilectum nobis in Chri&s;to, Jacobum Pylkington &s;acr$e the|clogiae haccalarium, in corum epi&s;copum et pa&s;torem elegerunt; cui quidem electioni et per&s;onae &s;ic electae, $$gium a&s;&s;en&s;um no&s;trum adhibuimus et favorem, ip&s;ui&s;&abque; &s;idelitatem nobis debitam pro dict$ epi&s;copatu re|$$pimus, ac temporalia eju&s;dem epi&s;copatus (exceptis manerio &s;ive dominio de Norham et Norham&s;hire cum &s;uis juribus membris et pertinentiis in comitatu no&s;tro Northumbriae necnon maneriis &s;ive dommiis de Allerton et Allerton&s;hire, ac dominio et manerio de Creke, cum &s;uis juribus membris et pertinentiis in com. $bortun; ac maneriis &s;ive dominiis de Sadbarghe, Mydleham, Ea&s;ington Ward, Ea&s;ington Coronator; Cot|ton Montyle and Gate&s;hed in com. palantino Dunolm. cum &s;uis juribus membris et pertinentiis; ac etiam omnibus me&s;&s;uagiis, domibus, aedificiis, molendinis, terris, pratis, pa&s;eis, pa&s;turis communiis, bo&s;eis, &s;ub|$$&s;eis, aquis, pi&s;cariis, parcis, warennis, cha&s;eis warennis, redditibus, &s;ervitiis, feodis milatum, wardis, mari|$agiis, e&s;caetis, advocationibus, juribus patronatuum eccle&s;ia$um, nundinis, tolnetis, mercatis, theo$ mis, $$&s;tumis, franch$&s;tis, libertatibus, privilegiis, pro&s;icuis, commoditatibus, emolume$tis et hereditamentis $$$bu&s;eumque cum pertinentiis, cuju&s;cumque &s;int generis natura$vel &s;peciei, dictis ma$$$iis &s;ive dominiis de Norham et Norham&s;hire in comitatu no&s;tro Northumbriae; ac man$riis &s;ive dominiis de Sadburgh, M$dle|$$m, E&s;ington Warde, E&s;ington Coronator, Cotton Monvyle et Gate$hed in co$nita$ pa$$$tino Dun$l$. $$$$uomodo &s;pectantibus &s;ive pertinentibus, aut ut membra partes &s;ive parcellas dic$o$m$ man$tio$um &s;ive $$minio$um habitis coguitis acceptis u&s;itatis &s;eu reputati$ exi&s;tentibus$ necnon om$ibus man$$$s terris $word$ mentis et hereditamentis, jacentibus et exi&s;tentibus in villis parochiis five hamlettis de Norham, Allerton, Creke, Sadburgh, Mydleham, E&s;ington Warde, E&s;ington Coronator, Cotton Monvyle et Gate&s;hed, in co|mitatibus Northumbriae et Eborum, et in comitatu palantino Dunolm.) Ei re&s;tituimus per prae&s;entes; et ideo tibi praecipimus, quod eidem electo, temporalia praedicta cum pertinentiis (exceptis praeexceptis) in bal|liva tua, una cum exitibus et proficuis inde a fe&s;to Sancti Michaelis archangeli ultimo praeterito, hucu&s;que provenientibus &s;ive cre&s;centibus, &s;ine dilatione liberes; &s;alvo jure cuju&s;libet. Te&s;te regina apud We&s;tmona|&s;terium, vice&s;imo quinto die Martii 1561. Per breve de privato &s;igillo.</P>
<P>Con&s;imilia brevia diriguntur e&s;caetoribus &s;ub&s;criptis &s;ub data praedicta, viz.</P>
