<P>He held the See of Durham only two years; died on the 6th of February 1631, aged 75, and was interred in St Paul's church, London. In this &s;hort period we find no memorable acts in the records of the palatinate<NOTE N="*" PLACE="foot">L. Gray's notes.&mdash;Ath. Ox. vol. i. p. 562.&mdash;Fuller's Worthies, (London) p. 207.&mdash;His Vi&s;itation Ar|ticles, anno 1629.&mdash;His daughter Ann married Tho. Farnabie the famous &s;choolma&s;ter, 2, A. O. 105, from whom de&s;cended Sir Cha. Farnabie, made a baronet A. D. 1726.
