<P>Gray's Minutes, MS.&mdash;Bi&s;hop Co&s;in gave 1174 books to the library of Peter Hou&s;e. Kennet's Reg. p. 327. &mdash;An account of his writing the Hi&s;tory of Tran&s;ub&s;tantiation. Kennet's Reg. p. 260.&mdash;His Speech to Charles II. at a meeting of bi&s;hops and prebends. Ibid. p. 283.&mdash;His Letter again&s;t bargaining for Eccle|&s;ia&s;tical Preferments. Ibid. p. 294.&mdash;His Behaviour at Durham. Ibid. p. 737, 885, 831.&mdash;His Letter to Jo&s;. Meade about his Book and Uproar at Edinburgh at fir&s;t reading Common Prayer-Book. Peek's De|&s;iderata, lib. ii. p. 50. Ibid lib. xiv. p. 45.&mdash;He gave ten books in folio, ten in quarto, and ten in octavo, to $he dean and chapter's library. His Life, written by Dr Theo. Smith.&mdash;See an account of his particu|lar benefactions in Sir Wm Dugdale's Hi&s;t. of the Ch. of D. annexed to the 2d edition of St Paul's C. 1715. &mdash;Ru&s;h worth's Col. p. iii. vol. i. p. 203, 203.&mdash;Pryn's Canterbury's Doom.&mdash;Walker's Hi&s;t. of the Suffering Clergy, vol. ii. p. 58.&mdash;Fuller's Ch. Hi&s;t. 1640, p. 173. Worthies, p. 295.&mdash;Heyl. Examen. Hi&s;t. p. 281.&mdash; Collyer' Supplement.&mdash;Nal&s;on's Col. p. 519, 520, 789.&mdash;Ath. Ox. vol. i. p. 636. vol. ii. p. 21, 339.&mdash;Biog. Brit. vol. iii. p. 1474.</P>
